          <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a></div>                              <h2>In Love and War</h2>                                                  <div class="clear-block">
            <div id="node-14" class="node">



  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
<div>Chivers Large Print</div>
<div>hardback May 2008, ISBN 978 1 405 64442 6</div>
<div>softback October 2008, ISBN 978 1 405 64443 3</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div><img hspace="10" vspace="10" align="left" src="/sites/default/files/In%20Love%20and%20War_0.jpg" width="100" height="159" />&nbsp;</div>
<div>Married to an inveterate gambler who is prepared to dispose of her life in order to pay his debts, Louise Oakingham flees, only to find herself torn between a husband she despises and a man she doubts.&nbsp;Is Captain Paul Fourier, on leave from the Peninsular campaign, her jailor or her saviour?&nbsp;It is ironic that the safest place for Louise is in the middle of a war, and in deciding to throw in her lot with the enigmatic captain, she begins to understand why women follow their men into battle.</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>  </div>

